{
  "text": "To give a concrete illustration of input determined automata, we show how the event clock automata of [CITATION_1] can be realized in the above framework. Take Op to be the set of operators {\u22b3 a , \u22b2 a | a \u2208 \u03a3}, where the operators \u22b3 a and \u22b2 a essentially record the time since the last a action, and the time to the next a action. The operator \u22b3 a (and similarly \u22b2 a ) can be defined here by setting \u22b3 a (\u03c3, i) to be {I \u2208 I Q | \u2203j < i : \u03c3(j) = a, \u03c4 (i) \u2212 \u03c4 (j) \u2208 I, and \u2200k : j < k < i, \u03c3(k) = a}.",
  "citation_candidates": [
